#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:3
#: 5df951a0bad94c4990d9528898e70bd4
msgid "Upgrading to R2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:6
#: bf82b141fa17400ba1de26c44e85cc4b
msgid ""
"Current Qubes R2 Beta 3 (R2B3) systems can be upgraded in-place to the "
"latest R2 (R2) release by following the procedure below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:8
#: 7029810ccb844db9956dc896d16df1af
msgid ""
"**Before attempting either an in-place upgrade or a clean installation, "
"we strongly recommend that users back up the system by using the built-"
"in** :doc:`backup tool </user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-"
"migrate>` **.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:11
#: 624e16d7e4884b3f8c37810ef8592a4e
msgid "Upgrade Template and Standalone VM(s)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:14
#: 18c5d4d848b344d29bf7a97602ee74dd
msgid ""
"Qubes R2 comes with new template based on Fedora 20. You can upgrade "
"existing template according to procedure described :ref:`here "
"<user/templates/fedora/fedora:upgrading>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:16
#: aad145be5a274becb471fc8985f3810f
msgid ""
"**It also possible to download a new Fedora 20-based template from our "
"repositories**. To do this please first upgrade the Dom0 distro as "
"described in the section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:20
#: 690ab6899e134cc1bb1e9cb650273d6e
msgid ""
"While technically it is possible to use old Fedora 18 template on R2, it "
"is strongly recommended to upgrade all the templates and Standalone VMs, "
"because Fedora 18 no longer receive security updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:22
#: 4b73922423f94b7b886f494b1b0f7452
msgid ""
"By default, in Qubes R2, there is only one template, however users are "
"free to create more templates for special purposes, as well as Standalone"
" VMs. If more than one template and/or Standalone VMs are used, then it "
"is recommended to upgrade/replace all of them. More information on using "
"multiple templates, as well as Standalone VMs, can be found :doc:`here "
"</user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:25
#: 6915a438b8004c0aacc7ef1890932839
msgid "Upgrading dom0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:28
#: 799f56d57f3a44149e2e69c190e45a5c
msgid ""
"Note that dom0 in R2 is based on Fedora 20, in contrast to Fedora 18 in "
"previous release, so this operation will upgrade a lot of packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:30
#: 4a237835f1c542788ac0840601758803
msgid "Open terminal in Dom0. E.g. Start->System Settings->Konsole."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:32
#: 5740a4ae3ad94f109f0abcd71716bf32
msgid "Install all the updates for Dom0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:42
#: c52cbe9167984ddd9100502fd9166db9
msgid ""
"After this step you should have ``qubes-release-2-5`` in your Dom0. "
"Important: if you happen to have ``qubes-release-2-6*`` then you should "
"downgrade to ``qubes-release-2-5``! The ``qubes-release-2-6*`` packages "
"have been uploaded to the testing repos and were kept there for a few "
"hours, until we realized they bring incorrect repo definitions and so we "
"removed them and also have changed the update procedure a bit "
"(simplifying it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:44
#: 15d7cce40e1e4aafa5b79f8e17c2b95b
msgid "Upgrade dom0 to R2:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:50
#: 28111185710645b79b72676c366cf0b1
msgid ""
"**Note:** be sure that the VM used as a update-downloading-vm (by default"
" its the firewallvm based on the default template) has been updated to "
"the latest Qubes packages, specifically ``qubes-core-vm-2.1.33`` or "
"later. This doesn’t imply that the VM must already be upgraded to fc20 – "
"for Dom0 upgrade we could still use an fc18-based VM (updatevm) it is "
"only important to install the latest Qubes packages there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:59
#: e4d8a977b6cf42d497912f7dbb628b28
msgid ""
"If above step completed successfully you should have ``qubes-"
"release-2-9`` or later. If not, repeat above step with additional "
"``--clean`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:65
#: 01ea005723aa4fd3b2a74e5f1b614e39
msgid ""
"4a. If you chose not to upgrade your fc18 templates, but instead to "
"download our new fc20-based template you should now be able to do that by"
" simply typing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:73
#: 304b73df48464d1f9aa311676f24edc0
msgid "Reboot the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/2.rst:79
#: 678e90eb0a2f4068a994ea5bd956f0cf
msgid ""
"Please note that if you use Anti Evil Maid, then it won’t be able to "
"unseal the passphrase this time, because the Xen, kernel, and initramfs "
"binaries have changed. Once the system boots up again, you could reseal "
"your Anti Evil Maid’s passphrase to the new configuration. Please consult"
" Anti Evil Maid documentation for explanation on how to do that."
msgstr ""

